# Cloudflare Pages headers — see https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# COOP/COEP enable SharedArrayBuffer in Workers. Pyodide doesn't strictly need
# SAB for v0.1, but having the headers in place means M5/M6 perf optimizations
# (e.g., transferring numpy buffers to the main thread without copies) won't
# require a follow-up infra PR.

/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

# Three.js, OBJLoader, and other CDN resources need cross-origin permissive policy
# to be loadable under COEP. They're served with CORS headers from jsDelivr.
# Pyodide CDN ditto. Browsers enforce this on a per-resource basis.

/*.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600

/css/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600

/models/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400, immutable
